research_municipality_step.notes: Manchester Township, NJ operates under the Mayor-Council system. Joseph Hankins was appointed Mayor on January 13, 2025, following the resignation of Robert Arace, and subsequently elected in November 2025 to complete the unexpired term ending December 31, 2026. Sandy Gravatt-Drake was appointed to the Township Council on January 28, 2025, to fill the unexpired term of Joseph Hankins. Terms for Council President Roxanne Conniff and Council Member Sandy Gravatt-Drake end December 31, 2026. Terms for Council Vice President James A. Vaccaro Sr., Council Member Michele Zolezi, and Council Member Craig A. Wallis end December 31, 2028, following their re-election in November 2024.
